Writing and Formatting Styles:
{
   "[Writing Styles] Likes": {"1": "Professional tone with clear legal terminology, e.g., 'The doctrine of prior appropriation governs water rights allocation.'", "2": "Concise wording to enhance clarity, e.g., 'Please find attached the relevant statutes.'", "3": "Use of bullet points for lists, e.g., 'Key issues include: 1. Allocation methods 2. Legal precedents.'", "4": "A respectful and collaborative tone when addressing partners, e.g., 'I appreciate your insights on this matter.'", "5": "Balanced valence, maintaining neutrality while discussing contentious topics."},
   "[Writing Styles] Dislikes": {"1": "Casual language or slang, e.g., 'Hey there, what's up with the water laws?'", "2": "Overly emotional language, e.g., 'I'm really upset about the recent ruling.'", "3": "Vague statements that lack specificity, e.g., 'You know, water stuff is important.'", "4": "Use of excessive emojis, e.g., 'Water rights are 🌊💧 very serious!'", "5": "Ambiguous terminology that could confuse the reader."},
   "[Formatting Styles] Likes": {"1": "Clear subject lines that indicate the email's purpose, e.g., 'Review of Water Allocation Case - [Case Name]'", "2": "Short paragraphs (2-3 sentences) to enhance readability.", "3": "Subsections within the email body for different topics, e.g., '1. Background 2. Current Legislation'.", "4": "Use of legal citations formatted correctly, e.g., 'See Water Code § 1001 for details.'", "5": "Professional email signature with full name and credentials."},
   "[Formatting Styles] Dislikes": {"1": "Long, dense paragraphs that overwhelm the reader.", "2": "Lack of headings or sections that can lead to confusion.", "3": "Informal sign-offs, e.g., 'Cheers!' or 'Later!'", "4": "Inconsistent formatting of names or titles, e.g., 'John Smith' vs 'Smith, J.'", "5": "Including unnecessary information that doesn't pertain to the topic at hand."}
